        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "   Most of the Germanic in English is",
          "   old — a thousand years or more. But",
          "   the borrowing never fully stopped.",
          "   Modern German has handed English a",
          "   small pile of words it couldn't do",
          "   without.",
          "",
          "   kindergarten  — children's garden",
          "   zeitgeist     — spirit of the time",
          "   wanderlust    — the ache to travel",
          "   doppelganger  — a ghostly double",
          "   schadenfreude — joy at another's",
          "                   misfortune",
          "",
          "   English took these without changing",
          "   them because nothing else said the",
          "   same thing. When a word is exactly",
          "   right, you don't translate it."
        ],
